This paper deals with natural language processing and semantic modeling, which are typically covered in the arXiv CS sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a new model for unifying tasks related to semantic relations and compositions, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The model uses vector space representations, which are commonly used in machine learning and natural language processing (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of the model for information retrieval and search, which falls under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper touches on the broader topic of semantics and meaning, which could be classified under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
